A question is followed by two statements numbered (I) and (II). You have to decide whether the data provided in the statements are sufficient to answer the question. Read both the statements and select the most appropriate answer. Question: Five friends, S, T, U, V and W, are of different ages. Who is the second eldest among them? Statements: (I) W is younger than T. W is elder than U. (II) T is the eldest. Only one person is younger than V.
options: Data in statements I and II together are sufficient to answer the question.
Data in statement I alone is sufficient to answer the question while data in statement II is not.
Data in statement II alone is sufficient to answer the question while data in statement I is not.
questions.answer: Data in statements I and II together are sufficient to answer the question.
